  "prompt": "Which phone should I buy under INR 15K?",
  "response": "As of October 2023, there are several excellent smartphones available under INR 15,000 in India. Here are some popular options you might consider:\n\n1. **Realme Narzo 60**:\n   - Features: MediaTek Dimensity 6020 processor, AMOLED display, decent camera setup, good battery life.\n\n2. **Poco X5**:\n   - Features: Snapdragon 695 processor, AMOLED display, solid gaming performance, good battery life.\n\n3. **Redmi Note 12**:\n   - Features: Snapdragon 685 processor, AMOLED display, good camera capabilities, 5,000mAh battery.\n\n4. **Samsung Galaxy M13**:\n   - Features: Exynos 850 processor, large display, good battery capacity, decent overall performance.\n\n5. **Moto G73**:\n   - Features: MediaTek Dimensity 930 processor, clean software experience, 120Hz display, good build quality.\n\n6. **Infinix Note 12**:\n   - Features: MediaTek Helio G88 processor, AMOLED display, decent camera performance, large battery.\n\nWhen choosing a phone, consider the following factors:\n\n- **Performance**: Look at the processor and RAM for smooth operation, especially for multitasking and gaming.\n- **Camera Quality**: Check for camera specifications if photography is essential for you.\n- **Battery Life**: A larger battery (around 5,000mAh) generally provides better endurance.\n- **Software Experience**: Opt for a phone with a clean UI and timely updates if possible.\n- **Display**: An AMOLED display offers better colors and contrast.\n\nAlways check online reviews and see if there are any new launches before making a decision. Prices may also vary based on sales or discounts, so keep an eye out for the best deals!",
